OL,3,CYellow cold-health alert issued for
OL,4,Cparts of the Midlands into the new year
OL,6,FPeople across the Midlands are being
OL,7,Furged to brace for chilly weather as a
OL,8,Fcold-health alert has been issued
OL,9,Facross parts of the region into the
OL,10,Fnew year.
OL,12,FThe Met Office has issued the warning
OL,13,Facross parts of the East and West
OL,14,FMidlands which is expected to be in
OL,15,Fplace until midday on January 5.
OL,17,FWeather bosses are urging people to
OL,18,Fplan ahead by keeping up to date with
OL,19,Fthe weather forecast, checking food
OL,20,Fand medicine stock and taking measures
OL,21,Fto reduce draughts at home.
